# Dashboard Proposal Table MDC Rules

- Table container: \`bg-white rounded w-full min-w-[600px]\`
- Table: \`w-full table-auto text-left border-collapse bg-white\`
- Header row: no background, no hover, sticky if needed
- Header cell:
  - \`text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary px-3 py-2 border-b border-primary border-opacity-20 text-left whitespace-nowrap\`
  - Right-align numeric, currency, and action columns: add \`text-right\`
- Body cell:
  - \`text-sm text-gray-700 px-3 py-2 whitespace-normal\`
  - Right-align numeric, currency, and action columns: add \`text-right\`
- Row: \`bg-white border-b border-primary border-opacity-10 last:border-b-0\`
- No row hover states
- Actions cell: \`flex gap-2 items-center justify-end\`
- Buttons in table:
  - Use \`<Button variant="outline" />\`
  - Add \`px-3 py-1 text-sm transition-colors duration-200 hover:text-[#7896CA] hover:border-[#7896CA]\`
- Spacing:
  - Use \`p-4\` for table container
  - Use \`gap-4\` or \`space-y-4\` for vertical rhythm in containers
- Typography:
  - Table body: \`text-base font-normal\`
  - Table header: \`text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary\`
- Accessibility:
  - All action buttons must have \`aria-label\`
  - Table must have a \`<caption>\` if used outside a card context
- No custom or inline styles; use only Tailwind utility classes

# Example usage:
- Use these rules for all data tables (Proposals, Loan Options, Users, etc.) for visual and UX consistency.
